description: Inherited from Middle English *redstert; equivalent to red +‎ start (“tail”). Compare Dutch roodstaart, Danish rødstjert.

entries.meaning: Any of various insectivorous ground-feeding birds, mainly of the genus Phoenicurus. Many of the species have a red tail.
(Canada, US) A not closely related species of warbler native to the Americas, Setophaga ruticilla
